Verbs + Objects

Objects are nouns or pronouns that come after verbs.

We can use verbs sing thank, invite, and ask with an indirect object.

I thanked him for the present.
(The indirect object of the verb phrase is him)

He asked her for the book.
(The indirect object of the verb phrase is her)

We invited them to the party.
(The indirect object of the verb phrase is them)

They asked Manny for advice.
(The indirect object of the verb phrase is Manny)

